      <body>
         <listPerson>
            <person xml:id="pers0843">
               <p>Mary, daughter of Sir <persName>Martin Westcomb</persName>, Consul of Cadiz,
                  married <persName>Bernard Granville</persName>, youngest brother of
                     <persName>George Granville</persName>, Lord Lansdowne. Her husband died in
                     <date when="1723">1723</date>, leaving her with two sons,
                     <persName>Bernard</persName> and <persName>Bevil</persName>, and two daughters,
                        <persName><ref target="/persons/pers0844.xml"/>Mary</persName> and
                        <persName><ref target="/persons/pers0842.xml"/>Ann</persName>. She then
                  settled with her daughters at <placeName>Buckland</placeName> in the
                     <placeName>Cotswolds</placeName>, where they became friends of the Kirkhams of
                     <placeName>Stanton</placeName>. From <placeName>Buckland</placeName> Mary and
                  her daughter <persName><ref target="/persons/pers0842.xml"/>Ann</persName> later
                  moved to <placeName>Gloucester</placeName>, while retaining their
                     <placeName>Cotswolds</placeName> friendships. Mrs. Granville died in <date
                     when="1747">1747</date>, and was buried in
                  <placeName>Gloucester</placeName>.</p>
            </person>
         </listPerson>
      </body>
   </text>
